<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142214" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole opaca var. incrustata Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole opaca var. incrustata Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="opaca" variety="incrustata">Pheidole opaca Mayr v. incrustata</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="variety">n. var.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="60" pageNumber="59">
[[ worker ]] L. 3,6 a 3,8 mill. Tete plus courte et, moins retrecie que chez l'opaca i. sp., sans former toutefois de bord posterieur. Sculpture comme chez la subsp. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142215" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole opaca subsp. sarrita Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole opaca subsp. sarrita Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="opaca" subSpecies="sarrita">sarrita</taxonomicName>
, mais encore plus serree, un peu moins grossiere, aussi profonde, avec plus de fines reticulations au fond, ce qui la rend moins luisante. Pattes tres finement reticulees-ponctuees et mates, de meme que l'abdomen et le pedicule, comme chez l´ 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142216" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole opaca Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole opaca Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opaca">opaca</taxonomicName>
typique. Tete d'un brun noiratre; le reste du corps un peu plus rougeatre; pattes, antennes et mandibules d'un brun un peu roussatre. Pilosite plus abondante que chez le type de l'espece.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="60">Tuis, Costa Rica (Pittier).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="60">
J'avais confondu jusqu'ici cette variete avec l´ 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142216" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole opaca Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole opaca Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opaca">opaca</taxonomicName>
typique. Mais sa sculpture fort differente, sa taille plus petite, sa couleur foncee et sa tete plus courte exigent une separation. A certains egards elle fait un peu transition a la subsp. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142215" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole opaca subsp. sarrita Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole opaca subsp. sarrita Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="opaca" subSpecies="sarrita">sarrita</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
